quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  70,19,Man is indeed impatient by nature
  70,20,When adversity touches him he bewails
  70,21,"And when prosperity touches him, he is begrudging"
  70,22,"But those who pray are not [so impatient]"
  70,23,Those that are constant in their prayers
  70,24,And those in whose wealth there is a known right
  70,25,For those that beg and for those that are deprived
  70,26,"And [among those who are not impatient are] those who sincerely believe in the Day of Judgment"
  70,27,And those that fear the punishment of their Lord
  70,28,— There is indeed no security against punishment of their Lord —
  70,29,And those that guard their chastity
  70,30,"Except from their spouses or from those whom they rightfully possess. For indulging in sex with them, they are, of course, not to be blamed"
  70,31,But whoever seeks to go beyond that — those are the ones that go beyond limits
  70,32,"And [among those who are not impatient are] those who are true to their trusts and who keep their word"
  70,33,And those who firmly stand by their testimonies
  70,34,And those who guard their prayer.h
  70,35,All those shall be the honoured ones in Gardens of Paradise
  70,36,And what is the matter with those that suppress the Truth that they rush to you
  70,37,"From the right and from the left, in groups"
  70,38,"Does everyone of them hope to enter the Garden of Bliss [by following one's own man- made thought]"
  70,39,"No, not at all! They know what We have created them from"
  70,40,"By no means [can they enter the Garden of Bliss!] I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests that We certainly are capable"
  70,41,Of replacing them by others better than they. And nothing can hinder Us
  70,42,"Leave them then to their vain talk and to their amusements, till they meet with the Day promised to them —"
  70,43,"The Day on which they will come hastily out of their graves, as though they had to run towards their goals"
  70,44,"Their eyes downcast and [their bodies] overwhelmed with disgrace! That is the Day they were promised"
  71,1,"We did indeed send Noah to his people: \"Warn your people before a painful punishment afflicts them"
  71,2,"He said, \"O my people! I am indeed sent to give you a plain warning"
  71,3,"That you should worship Allah, and fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"HE will forgive you some of your sins, and give you respite till an appointed time. When the Allah appointed time comes, it cannot be deferred, if only you knew"
  71,5,"[Noah later] said, \"My Lord! I have indeed preached to my people night and day"
  71,6,My preaching however has only drove them farther away
  71,7,"And, indeed, whenever I preached to them [to come to the Right Path] so that You might forgive them, they put their fingers into their ears, covered themselves up in their garments, grew obstinate, and became arrogant with false pride"
  71,8,And I did indeed preach to them loud and clear
  71,9,And then I spoke to them in public; and I confided to them privately
  71,10,"And I said, `Ask your Lord to forgive you. He is indeed most forgiving"
  71,11,He will make the sky pour rain on you in abundance
  71,12,"And He will help you with wealth and children, and will make gardens for you, and will generate rivers for you"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you do not attribute Grandeur to Allah
  71,14,"And He has surely created you [mankind] of diverse sorts and conditions"
  71,15,Do you not see how Allah has created seven heavens one over another
  71,16,"And He has made within these, the moon a light [reflected], and the sun, a [radiant] lamp"
  71,17,And Allah has grown you from the earth like a plant
  71,18,"Thereafter He will restore you to it [when you die]. And He will bring you out in resurrection"
  71,19,And Allah has made the earth spread out for you
  71,20,So that you might thread thereon a network of spacious paths
  71,21,"Noah said, \"My Lord! They have disobeyed me all along, and they follow one whose wealth and children increase nothing but their loss"
  71,22,And they plotted a great plot
  71,23,"And they told [their followers], \"Abandon not your gods: abandon not Wadd, Suwa', Yaghuth, Ya'uq or Nasr"
  71,24,"And they have verily led many astray. And [O Allah] increase nothing but their delusion for these wicked people"
  71,25,"They [those wicked persons] were drowned because of their sins, and are doomed to enter the Fire [in the Hereafter]. And they found none to help them against Allah"
  71,26,"And Noah prayed, \"My Lord! Leave not any of those who suppress the Truth to inhabit on the earth"
  71,27,"If You do indeed leave them, they will lead those who worship You astray, and will give birth to none but wicked and ingrate progeny"
  71,28,"My Lord! Grant forgiveness to me, to my parents, to everyone who enters my house as a believer, and to all believing men and women. And grant increase in nothing buttheir destruction for the wicked people"